main event: Military and civilian observers reported multiple sightings of unidentified lights and objects in the sky over South Carolina and Puerto Rico on January 29, 1962.
interesting points: An aircraft reported an intense light above and southeast of its position, causing it to divert off course.
Another aircraft, en route from Ramey Air Force Base, observed an intense light northwest of its position.
Ground observers reported seeing a greenish glow heading northwest through east, as well as a light moving northwest to south-southeast.
The Air Force indicated the lights were likely part of a missile test, AFMTC 119/1, conducted during the same time period.
The sightings were reported to various military commands, including NORAD, the U.S. Air Force, and the U.S. Navy.
sighted object: Unidentified lights and objects in the sky
photographs: No photographs were included in the report.
